                                    <!-- FAQ Section for AEO -->
                                    <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>What is GEO (Generative Engine Optimization)?</h3>
                                        <p>GEO is the discipline of optimising content for visibility inside AI-generated answers across ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Gemini, Google AI Overviews and Microsoft Copilot. It is the broader successor to SEO for the AI-search era.</p>
                                        <h3>Is GEO different from AEO?</h3>
                                        <p>AEO (Answer Engine Optimization) is the citation-targeting subset of GEO. GEO is the umbrella that includes AEO plus broader tactics like model-training-data influence, snippet readiness, and RAG-friendliness. Most agencies use both terms interchangeably; GEO is more comprehensive.</p>
                                        <h3>Will GEO replace SEO in 2026?</h3>
                                        <p>No. SEO still drives 70%+ of organic traffic in 2026. AI search drives 22-30% of informational queries and is growing. The right strategy is layered: keep your SEO investment, add GEO retrofits on top of high-performing content.</p>
                                        <h3>How do I retrofit existing SEO content for GEO?</h3>
                                        <p>Audit your top 50 pages. For each, add a TL;DR box, convert 3+ H2s to question format, add an FAQ block with FAQPage schema, update date-stamps and stale stats, and add author schema. Plan 4-6 hours per page; ROI in 60-120 days.</p>
                                        <h3>Which GEO tools should I use in 2026?</h3>
                                        <p>Paid options: Profound, AthenaHQ, Semrush AI Search, BrightEdge AEO module, Otterly.AI. Free option: monthly manual audit querying 50 priority keywords across ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity and Gemini and tracking citation appearance.</p>
